Working with java in Linux

Step1:
Update OS

$sudo  apt  update


Step2:

Install  ssh

$sudo apt install   ssh

Step3

Installing java in linux

$ sudo apt  install default-jdk 

open JDK 8
$sudo apt   install openjdk-8-jdk

open JDK 9

$ sudo apt   install openjdk-9-jdk

Default location of java installation




Java path setting

Go to home directory 

$cd 

$ls –a  🡪 to display all files including hidden files
You  can see the  “.bashrc” file

$gedit .bashrc

  (or)

$gedit  ~/.bashrc


export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64

export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin

Writing  Java program

$gedit Test.java

//import java.lang.*;  optional package

public class Test
{

   public static void main(String []args)
   {

	System.out.println("Hello World");
   }

} 

Compilation

$javac Test.java

Execution
$java Test

installing eclipse 

$ sudo  apt  install  eclipse


Working with mysql in linux

Installing mysql in linux

$sudo apt   install  mysql-server  mysql-client

Connect to mysql server

$mysql  –u  root   -p
Password : ********

Mysql>show databases

Mysql>create database  mnrao

Mysql>use mnrao

Mysql>select database() from dual

Mysql>show tables

